{
  "texts": [
    "(i) There is some i ∈ {1,..., N -1} such that for everyx ∈ Q i = [ (i-1)c N, ic N] × [0, c N] d-1 ∥h(x + c N e 1) -h(x) -1N (h(ce 1) -h(0))∥ ≤ cε N;(ii) There is some z which lies simultanously in the lattice c N M Z d and in the set[0, c - c N M] × [0, c N - c N M] d-1 such that ∥h(z + c N M e 1) -h(z)∥ c N M > (1 + φ) ∥h(ce 1) -h(0)∥ c.Proof of Lemma 5.8.",
    "Let N, M and φ be the constants obtained in [22,Lemma 3.3].",
    "Let us call, for the purposes of the proof, points which lie simultanously in the lattice c N M Z d and in the set[0, c - c N M] × [0, c N - c N M] d-1,lattice points.",
    "Note that there are only finitely many lattice points.",
    "We denote by P n: ℓ 2 → R n the orthogonal projection to span{e 1,..., e n }."
  ]
